              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron energy was determined by time of flight.",
                "The time structure of the neutron beam is typically",
                "set to a 100 Hz macropulse structure containing about",
                "375 micropulses of 250 ps in width, each spaced",
                "by 1.8mu-s.The start signal is the proton pulse hitting",
                "the spallation target and the stop signal is fragment",
                "detection by the central cathode of the TPC chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission fragments were detected using fission",
                "time projection chamber. It consists of two identical",
                "gas volumes separated by central cathode plane.",
                "Measured actinide targets were placed on the cathode",
                "plane. Each gas volume has a highly segmented anode",
                "with 2976 hexagonal readout pads, 2 mm in pitch. The",
                "drift chamber was filled with 95% argon/5% isobutane",
                "at 550 torr. Pads were read-out using MICROMEGAS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons with unmoderated white flux were",
                "produced by spallation reaction of 800 MeV protons on",
                "tungsten target."
              ]
            }
          ],
